{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"b64bdeee-b6a2-41f1-9109-a0dd0bfa59d5","content":"The working directory is empty — there's no repository or template files here to inspect.\n\nHowever, I can answer from knowledge of the standard .NET templates (`dotnet new webapi` and `dotnet new webapp`):\n\n## Side-by-Side Comparison\n\n| Feature | `webapi` | `webapp` |\n|---------|----------|----------|\n| **Authentication (`--auth`)** | ✅ Yes (None, Individual, IndividualB2C, SingleOrg, Windows) | ✅ Yes (same options) |\n| **Native AOT (`--aot`)** | ✅ Yes (.NET 8+) | ❌ No |\n| **Framework** | `--framework` | `--framework` |\n| **Use controllers** | `--use-controllers` | N/A |\n| **Minimal APIs** | Default (minimal) | N/A (Razor Pages) |\n| **HTTPS (`--no-https`)** | ✅ | ✅ |\n| **Use Program.Main** | `--use-program-main` | `--use-program-main` |\n| **OpenAPI (`--no-openapi`)** | ✅ | ❌ |\n| **Docker** | `--use-docker` | `--use-docker` |\n\n### Key Differences\n\n- **Authentication**: Both support `--auth`.\n- **AOT**: Only `webapi` supports `--aot` (Native AOT compilation). Razor Pages in `webapp` aren't compatible with AOT.\n- `webapi` is API-focused (minimal APIs or controllers); `webapp` generates a Razor Pages UI app.\n\nTo see the full parameter list yourself, run:\n```\ndotnet new webapi --help\ndotnet new webapp --help\n```","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"d435a7a0-8038-4bbd-a5e6-aa20c242e9e9","outputTokens":411,"requestId":"782F:3EF0C4:714BA22:7D9C7F8:69F3FA0C"},"id":"84d40cec-110d-45e9-8f1c-f7a32291f093","timestamp":"2026-05-01T00:56:04.944Z","parentId":"e2b39f42-52fa-40a0-9ba8-6d988d9fd618"}
